DEPUTY First Minister Nicola Sturgeon has helped a fast-food outlet in Glasgow win a litter picking award. Litter prize for fast-food spot DEPUTY First Minister Nicola Sturgeon has helped a fast-food outlet in Glasgow win a litter picking award.McDonald's in Govanhill won a Scotland-wide award for cleaning up the area, a scheme which attracted the participation of Ms Sturgeon.The restaurant is now in the running for a UK award. 